Private Half Day Fly Fishing Trips
Apr-Nov, $150 to $175 per person


Beginners and seasoned veterans alike can enjoy a memorable morning or afternoon with an expert fly fishing guide casting on scenic Yosemite waterways.
Family Fun HALF DAY
Get a taste of Yosemite fly fishing on local waters on this fun half day adventure perfect for the whole family! This basic introduction focuses less on instruction and more on the experience of fly fishing, as well as aquatic ecology and conservation with many opportunities to sustainably catch and release trout along the river banks of our favorite local spots. Boots and waders are not provided as we focus solely on czech nymphing from the river bank!  7AM or 3PM start times; 4 hours, $150 per person.
Experienced Angler's Private Half Day
Already know the basics!? Join our local guides and gain access to the best waters in the Sierra for native Rainbow Trout and wild Brook trout and trophy Brown trout. We can help sharpen your cast, share tips and techniques, or just provide the right fly for the right fish.  7AM or 3PM start times;  5 hours, $175 per person.
Evergreen & Rush Creek Lodges work with amazing agencies such as Echo Adventure Cooperative and Yosemite Outfitters to provide top quality fishing experiences on the Yosemite area waterways.
Beginner-Advanced Effort, Ages 7+, Half Day, Sunrise, Sunset


Beginners and seasoned veterans alike can enjoy a memorable morning or afternoon with an expert fly fishing guide casting on scenic Yosemite waterways. Family Fun HALF...


More   Book Now




Private Full Day Fly Fishing Trips
Apr-Nov, $215 to $300 per person


Beginners and seasoned veterans alike can enjoy a memorable morning or afternoon with an expert Yosemite fly fishing guide casting on scenic Yosemite waterways.
Introduction to fly fishing
Our private Introduction to Fly fishing trip is perfect for individuals, families or groups that want to learn the basics of fly fishing during their visit to Yosemite National Park! This beginner trip focuses on beginner casting, fly selection, reading water and basic knot tying. As well as Czech Nymphing, dry fly, streaming and wet fly techniques. 7AM or Noon start times; 8 hours, $230 per person.
Experienced anglers private full day
Enjoy the best of the Yosemite area on our full day fly fishing adventure for intermediate and advanced anglers. Whether you want to try for the illusive Golden Trout in Yosemite's backcountry or spend your day in the iconic splendor of Yosemite Valley, our private guide can help you achieve all of your fishing goals! 7AM or Noon start times; 8 hours, $215 per person.
Private high Country Fly Fishing Adventure
**Note: Seasonal road dependent, Tioga Road usually opens mid-June.**  This amazing day is spent above 8000 feet in Yosemite's pristine high country and is perfect for the adventurous angler! We'll take you far away from the crowds for a classic fly fishing experience on untouched, high alpine lakes and streams in search of wild trout and unprecedented views of Yosemite's tallest peaks. Note: There is 2-6 miles of hiking at high altitude on this trip. 8AM start times; 10 hours, $300 per person.
Evergreen & Rush Creek Lodges work with amazing agencies such as Echo Adventure Cooperative and Yosemite Outfitters to provide top quality fishing experiences on the Yosemite area waterways.
